msgid "blurgle"
msgstr "blurgle"

#: ../../B/blurgle.rst:7
msgid "/bler´gl/, n\\."
msgstr "/bler´gl/, 名詞"

#: ../../B/blurgle.rst:9
msgid ""
"[UK] Spoken :ref:`metasyntactic-variable`\\, to indicate some text that is "
"obvious from context, or which is already known. If several words are to be "
"replaced, blurgle may well be doubled or tripled. \"To look for something in"
" several files use ‘grep string blurgle blurgle’.\" In each case, \"blurgle "
"blurgle\" would be understood to be replaced by the file you wished to "
"search. Compare :ref:`mumble`\\, sense 7."
msgstr ""
"[英国]話し言葉の\\ :ref:`metasyntactic-variable`\\ "
"で、文脈から明白な、あるいはすでに分かっているテキストを示すのに使う。複数の単語を置き換える場合、blurgleは2回や3回重ねられることもある。「複数のファイルの中で何かを探すには‘grep"
" string blurgle blurgle’を使え」。それぞれの場合で、「blurgle "
"blurgle」は、あなたが検索したいファイルに置き換わるものと理解される。\\ :ref:`mumble`\\ の語義7と比較せよ。"
